'''古拉尼人'''（[[古拉尼語|古拉尼語]]：Горанци / ''Goranci''）是居住在橫跨[[科索沃|科索沃]]、[[北馬其頓|北馬其頓]]、[[阿爾巴尼亞|阿爾巴尼亞]]三國的{{link-en|古拉地區|Gora (region)}}的一個[[民族|民族]]，他們是[[南部斯拉夫民族|南部斯拉夫民族]]的一支，大多信仰[[伊斯蘭教|伊斯蘭教]]。過去曾視他們是[[波士尼亞人|波士尼亞人]]、[[塞爾維亞人|塞爾維亞人]]、[[保加利亞人|保加利亞人]]、[[馬其頓人|馬其頓人]]、[[土耳其人|土耳其人]]的一部分<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=GCRjKdrmqqEC&pg=PA211&dq=gorani+bulgarian+passports |title=Kosovo: the Bradt travel guide, Gail Warrander, Verena Knaus, Published by Bradt Travel Guides, 2007, ISBN 1841621994, p. 211. |access-date=2014-12-30 |archive-date=2019-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224123412/https://books.google.com/books?id=GCRjKdrmqqEC&pg=PA211&dq=gorani+bulgarian+passports |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Fnbw1wsacSAC&pg=PA70&dq=Gorani+are+Muslim+Slavs |title=Historical dictionary of Kosova, Robert Elsie, Scarecrow Press, 2004, ISBN 0810853094, p. 70. |access-date=2014-12-30 |archive-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206084512/https://books.google.com/books?id=Fnbw1wsacSAC&pg=PA70&dq=Gorani+are+Muslim+Slavs |dead-url=no }}</ref>。古拉尼人的一部分已經被[[阿爾巴尼亞|阿爾巴尼亞]]化<ref>Bulgarians in the region of Korcha and Mala Prespa (Albania) nowadays, Balkanistic Forum (1-3/2005), South-West University "Neofit Rilski", Blagoevgrad, Pashova, Anastasija Nikolaeva; Issue: 1-3/2005, Page Range: 113-130.</ref>。在1991年南斯拉夫的人口普查中，他們自稱為[[穆斯林族|穆斯林族]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=aJRYkzl5YC4C&pg=PA27&dq=pomaks+gora&lr= |title=Religion and the politics of identity in Kosovo by Gerlachlus Duijzings, C. Hurst & Co. Publishers, 2000, ISBN 185065431X,  p. 27. |access-date=2014-12-30 |archive-date=2019-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221111844/https://books.google.com/books?id=aJRYkzl5YC4C&pg=PA27&dq=pomaks+gora&lr= |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在馬其頓共和國，古拉尼人的民族認同因宗教信仰而大不相同<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=ppbuavUZKEwC&pg=PA209&dq=gora+torbeshi&lr= Who are the Macedonians? by Hugh Poulton, edition: 2, revised, C. Hurst & Co. Publishers, 2000, ISBN 1850655340, p. 209.]</ref>。

